@AleMercadal also, you can do it via config(`$config['container']['definitions']`)
> Or should i declare the behavior into every controller instead?

Right way is create your base web controller extends by module controllers:
~~~php
abstract class BaseController extends Controller
{
  /**
   * @var string[]|true
   */
  public $publicActions = true;

  public function behaviors()
  {
      $behaviors = parent::behaviors();

      if ($this->publicActions !== true) {
          $behaviors['auth'] = [
              'class' => CompositeAuth::class,
              'except' => $this->publicActions,
              'authMethods' => [...]
          ];
      }

      return $behaviors;
  }
}
~~~
